### InterviewCoach API — REST Client Tests
### Install "REST Client" extension in VS Code to run these

@base = http://localhost:8000

### Health Check
GET {{base}}/health

###

### Get Azure Speech Token
GET {{base}}/api/speech/token

###

### Evaluate an Answer (test without file upload)
POST {{base}}/api/interview/evaluate
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "question": "Tell me about your experience with Python and FastAPI.",
  "answer": "I have been working with Python for 3 years. I built RESTful APIs using FastAPI and deployed them on Azure App Service. I also used SQLAlchemy for database interactions.",
  "job_role": "Backend Developer",
  "resume_context": "Python developer with 3 years experience in FastAPI, SQLAlchemy, Azure"
}

###

### Get Interview Summary
POST {{base}}/api/interview/summary
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "job_role": "Backend Developer",
  "questions_and_answers": [
    {
      "question": "Explain how FastAPI handles async requests.",
      "answer": "FastAPI is built on Starlette and uses Python async/await to handle concurrent requests without blocking the event loop.",
      "score": 82
    },
    {
      "question": "Describe a challenging project you worked on.",
      "answer": "I built a real-time notification system using WebSockets and Redis pub/sub for 10,000 concurrent users.",
      "score": 75
    }
  ]
}
